          <head>
            <note type="contents-note">This manuscript contains: The four Gospels according to the Peshitta version. In total, including sub-sections, this manuscript contains 5 items.</note>
            <listRelation type="Wright-BL-Taxonomy">
              <relation name="dcterms:type" ref="http://purl.org/dc/terms/type" active="https://bl.syriac.uk/ms/742" passive="#bible-nt">
                <desc>New Testament</desc>
              </relation>
            </listRelation>
          </head>
          <msContents>
            <textLang mainLang="syr">Syriac</textLang>
            <msItem xml:id="a1" n="1" defective="true">
              <locus from="1a" to="211a">Foll. 1a-211a</locus>
              <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/71" xml:lang="en">The four Gospels according to the Pĕshīṭtā version</title>
              <finalRubric xml:lang="syr">ܫܠ̣ܡ ܛܛܪܐܘܢܓܠܝܘܢ ܡܬܝ܀ ܡܪܩܘܣ ܠܘܩܐ܀ ܝܘܚܢܢ ..</finalRubric>
              <note>The Ammonian sections and Eusebian canons are marked in the text in the usual way, and there is a harmony at the foot of each page. The larger sections are indicated by the letter <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܨ</foreign> on the margins or between the columns. Many of the lessons are rubricated in the text.</note>
              <msItem xml:id="b1" n="2" defective="true">
                <locus from="1a" to="50">Foll. 1a-50</locus>
                <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/72" xml:lang="en">Matthew</title>
                <note>The missing portions are: ch. i. 1—v. 16, x. 16—xii. 11, and xii. 44—xiv. 3.</note>
              </msItem>
              <msItem xml:id="b2" n="3">
                <locus from="50a" to="89">Foll. 50a-89</locus>
                <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/73" xml:lang="en">Mark</title>
              </msItem>
              <msItem xml:id="b3" n="4">
                <locus from="89a" to="158">Foll. 89a-158</locus>
                <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/74" xml:lang="en">Luke</title>
              </msItem>
              <msItem xml:id="b4" n="5">
                <locus from="158a" to="211a">Foll. 158a-211a</locus>
                <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/75" xml:lang="en">John</title>
              </msItem>
            </msItem>
          </msContents>
          <physDesc>
            <p>Vellum, about 12 7/8 in. by 9 3/4, of 211 leaves, a few of which are stained and torn, especially foll. 1, 11, 120, 210, and 211. The quires are 24 in number, but only one leaf now remains of the first, and two leaves of the third. They were originally signed with both letters and arithmetical figures (e.g. foll. 14 a,ܕ; 24 a, ܗ; 50a, ܚ; 60a, ܛ; 100a, ܝܓ; 140 a, ܝܙ; 158 a, ܝܛ; 178 a, ܟܐ), but have since been incorrectly renumbered with letters only. Each page is divided into two columns, of from 19 to 24 lines. </p>
            <objectDesc form="codex">
              <supportDesc material="perg">
                <support>
                  <material>Vellum</material>
                </support>
                <extent>
                  <measure type="composition" unit="leaf" quantity="211">211 ff.</measure>
                  <dimensions type="leaf" unit="inch">
                    <height quantity="12.875">12 7/8</height>
                    <width quantity="9.75">9 3/4</width>
                  </dimensions>
                </extent>
                <collation>
                  <p>The quires are 24 in number. They were originally signed with both letters and arithmetical figures (e.g. foll.<locus from="14a" to="14a">14 a</locus>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܕ</foreign>;<locus from="24a" to="24a">24 a</locus>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܗ</foreign>;<locus from="50a" to="50a">50a</locus>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܚ</foreign>;<locus from="60a" to="60a">60a</locus>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܛ</foreign>;<locus from="100a" to="100a">100a</locus>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܓ</foreign>;<locus from="140a" to="140a">140 a</locus>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܙ</foreign>;<locus from="158a" to="158a">158 a</locus>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܝܛ</foreign>;<locus from="178a" to="178a">178 a</locus>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܟܐ</foreign>).</p>
                </collation>
                <condition>
                  <list>
                    <item>
                      <p>A few leaves are stained and torn, especially foll.<locus from="1" to="1">1</locus>, <locus from="11" to="11">11</locus>, <locus from="120" to="120">120</locus>, <locus from="210" to="211">210, and 211</locus>.</p>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                      <p>Only one leaf now remains of the first quire, and two leaves of the third.</p>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </condition>
              </supportDesc>
              <layoutDesc>
                <layout columns="2" writtenLines="19 24">
                  <p>Each page is divided into two columns, of from 19 to 24 lines.</p>
                </layout>
              </layoutDesc>
            </objectDesc>
            <handDesc hands="4">
              <handNote xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr-Syre" medium="unknown">
                The writing is a large, regular Esṭrangĕlā of the <date notBefore="0500" notAfter="0700">6th or 7th century</date>.
              </handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote2" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                Of the <date notBefore="0800" notAfter="0900">9th century</date>. <ref target="#addition2">See additions.</ref>
                </handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote3" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                <ref target="#addition1">See additions.</ref>
                </handNote>
              <handNote xml:id="handNote4" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                <ref target="#addition3">See additions.</ref>
                </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <additions>
              <note type="proofreader-note">N.B., folio location may not be available for some items below.</note>
              <list>
                <item xml:id="addition1" n="1">
                  <ref target="#handNote3"/>
                  <p>The quires have since been incorrectly renumbered with letters only.</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition2" n="2">
                  <locus from="211" to="211"/>
                  <ref target="#handNote2"/>
                  <p>Fol. 211 is written by a hand of the <date notBefore="0800" notAfter="0900">9th century</date>, and was probably added by the same person who retouched many portions of the older text.</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition3" n="3">
                  <ref target="#handNote4"/>
                  <p>Other lessons have been noted by different hands on the margins.</p>
                </item>
                <item xml:id="addition4" n="4">
                  <locus from="211a" to="211a"/>
                  <ref target="#handNote2"/>
                  <p>On fol. 211 a, after the doxology, there stands a note, informing us that the manuscript belonged to the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/360">convent of S. Mary Deipara</placeName> in the <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/289">desert of Scete</placeName>.</p>
                  <p>
                    <quote xml:lang="syr">ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܐܘܢܓܠܝܘܢ ܗܢܐ ܩܕܝܫܐ .. ܕܕܝܪܐ ܕܣܘܪ̈ܝܝܐ ܕܒܡܕܒܪܐ ܕܒܡܨܪܝܢ ܕܗ̣ܘ ܐܝܬܘܗܝ ܡܕܒܪܐ ܕܐܣܩ̈ܛܝܣ ܕܝܪܐ ܕܝܠܗܘܢ ܐܝܬܝܗ̇ ܥܠ ܫܡܐ ܩܕܝܫܐ ܕܒܬܘܠܬܐ ܝܠܕܬ ܐܠܗܐ ܡܪܝܡ ܕܒܨ̈ܠܘܗ̇ ܩܕܝܫ̈ܬܐ ܢܫܟ݁ܢ ܠܢ ܪ̈ܚܡܐ ܘܚܢܢܐ ܒܝܘܡܐ ܕܡܬܓܠܝܢܘܬܗ ܫܒܝܚܬܐ ܕܡܫܝܚܐ ܐܠܗܐ ܣܒܪܐ ܕܟܪ̈ܣܛܝܢܐ. ܏ܘܫ</quote>
                  </p>
                </item>
              </list>
            </additions>
